<p>Keyword research for the Kenyan market is fundamentally different from international keyword research, not because the tools are different, but because Kenyan search volumes are smaller, Swahili search behaviour adds a second language layer, and local modifiers (county names, estate names, neighbourhood-level terms, and "near me" patterns in the Kenyan context) require a Kenya-specific approach that global keyword guides do not address. A keyword that gets 50 monthly searches in Nairobi can represent significant revenue for a local service business.</p>

